snippet.textDisplay: Ali Sethi did a decent job with improvisations from Jaffer's help. All in all it was a good effect on ears. For people who are comparing this to Papon's version (from Indian Coke Studio), Ghazal singing is not only about singing quality but also a major thing that contributes to its beauty is Urdu pronunciation.  Papon's version is one of the worst pronunciation of Urdu ghazals I have ever heard in an official studio setting (one can ignore or pardon reality show singers for bad pronunciation). He may be an accomplished singer but he doesn't know Urdu. Ghazal singer has to have command on Urdu poetry pronunciation or else he or she will ruin it for good. That's what Papon did from first minute onwards.
